{"sections":[{"xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26.4","image":"ic_component_intro.png","title":"Use your first OUDS components","backgroundImage":"ic_component_intro.png","projectFiles":"OUDS-Discovery-Tutorial.zip","kind":"hero","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS provides components ready to be used, specified in Figma assets and preventing users to handle tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"They are rendered thanks to the theme in use."}]}],"chapter":"Use of first components provided by OUDS","estimatedTimeInMinutes":30},{"tasks":[{"contentSection":[{"mediaPosition":"trailing","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We will work on a kind of formular using main OUDS components.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Feel free to style and design things as you want.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"contentAndMedia"}],"title":"Add basic components","stepsSection":[{"caption":[],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-1.swift","runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"First, prepare the ","type":"text"},{"code":"ContentView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" by adding inside it a ","type":"text"},{"code":"ScrollView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"media":null,"type":"step"},{"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Now, let’s add radio buttons to let the user choose its gender."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The official components are "},{"code":"OUDSRadio","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSRadioItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", but the package has also a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSRadioPicker"},{"text":" to implement quicky a group of radios.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This component can be replaced by your own."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The radio picker is defined by an array of values to display radio items associated to a tag, i.e. an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Hashable"},{"text":" thing shared through a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Inside a picker the user can select only one value, not zero."}]}],"type":"step","caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add such picker with three items inside."}]}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-2.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-2.png"},{"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The radio picker is alone, it is the time to add below a checkbox. OUDS provides two components: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSCheckbox"},{"text":" which is a simple checkbox, and ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which is a checkbox (duh!) with additional texts and icons.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The state of the checkbox is shared through a boolean "},{"code":"State","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In some cases you may need to use ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxIndeterminate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if you want a three-states checkbox."}]}],"type":"step","caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add a checkbox item with only two states.","type":"text"}]}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-3.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-3.png"},{"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There are also components who do not have any behaviors and are here only for visual rendering, for example dividers which can be horizontal or vertical.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A divider is, in the end, a stroke with a color. You will see later, colors in OUDS have two values: a light mode value, and a dark mode value. Here the divider can have a color which can change, or not.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"step","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Choose to add an instance of ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSHorizontalDivider","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-4.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-4.png"},{"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With radio and checkbox, OUDS provides also switch elements (toggles). They can be alone ("},{"code":"OUDSSwitch","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") or with texts ("},{"code":"OUDSSwitchItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Just like the checkbox, the switch exposes its state through a "},{"code":"Binding","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"type":"step","caption":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add a switch item, it will be used as a trick to force the change of the color scheme for the view for our future operations."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You will then be able to see the automatic changes of colors when you switch the color scheme."}]}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-5.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-5.png"},{"media":null,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Users may need to navigate outside the app, like, for example, opening a website. Thus the "},{"code":"OUDSLink","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" component can be integrated. It can be only with a text or also a chevron indicator."}]}],"type":"step","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add an ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSLink","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the app and make it open the iOS documentation OUDS website.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-6.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-6.png"},{"caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s add a button with some rules: if checkbox is not checked it is disabled. When tapped, change the style of the button during 5 seconds."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"code":"tutorial-discovery-3-7.swift","runtimePreview":"tutorial-discovery-3-7.png","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In the end, we can also add a button. Button are one of the most used components in an app and bring a lof of the power and the style of the brand.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can find it with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"OUDSButton","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Such button has an appearance changing its colors, and also a style (loading or not).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Thanks to the theme, the enabled, disabled, hover, focus or pressed states are managed.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"media":null,"type":"step"}],"anchor":"Add-basic-components"}],"kind":"tasks"},{"kind":"assessments","anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding","assessments":[{"choices":[{"isCorrect":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"No! The components use the design specifications, i.e. tokens, thanks to the theme, to define the style they must have in all cases.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":true,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No"}]}],"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That is the reason why the "},{"code":"OUDSThemeableView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is so important: it injects the theme as environment variable so that any component can get it to define its style."}]}]}],"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Does the developer using OUDS component need to manage the look and feel of the components?"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"multiple-choice","content":[]}]},{"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial","title":"Add more OUDS components","kind":"callToAction","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Components can be similar to iOS native components, or can also be original and strongly related to Orange Unified Design System needs."}],"action":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-4-use-other-components","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Get started","type":"text"}],"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Get started"}}],"kind":"project","hierarchy":{"modules":[{"projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-1-package-and-librairies#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}]}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies"},{"projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme#Basic-structure-for-the-app","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-discovery-2-instanciate-theme#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"assessment"}]}],"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Preparation-of-the-theme"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents-(discovery)\/Use-of-first-components-provided-by-OUDS","projects":[{"sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContrac